HEADWORD: Ophthalmia
<hw>Oph*thal"mi*a</hw> <pr>(⟦ocr⟧f*th⟦acr⟧l"m⟦icr⟧*⟦adot⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>ophthalmie</ets>, L. <ets>ophthalmia</ets>,
fr. Gr. <grk>'ofqalmi`a</grk>, fr. <grk>'ofqalmo`s</grk> the eye, akin
to E. <ets>optic</ets>. See <er>Optic</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>An inflammation of the membranes or coats of the eye or of the
eyeball.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> ophthalmitis.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

